name: Hotel Bali Mega
address: Komplek Perumahan Taman Griya, Jl.Batur Raya, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Stayed a few times. Great position, clean pool, friendly staff.
review 2: Great value for money. This is a budget hotel but with all the comforts one needs. It is brand new, modern, clean and has a nice bed. The rooms also have a desk, which I found convenient for working. The hotel is only 15 min  by motorbike to the gorgeous Jimbaram beach and outside on the main road there's lots of options for food and mini mart. The staff is also very nice. You can rent motorbike with them.
review 3: Basic hotel where I was the only western guest. Full of local tourist and thats why the place was super noisy when kids where yelling in the pool and running in the hallways. Staff was friendly, breakfast good but location is not the best.
review 4: Good hotel with comfortable rooms. The toilet is clean. The AC is also cool. The swimming pool was nice and fun to swim at.
review 5: Great place, very clean room and staff is amazing, very polite and available for any request. The laundry service is excellent! At a very affordable price!

name: Waroeng Kampoeng Chinese Food & Seafood
address: Jl. Nuansa II, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
We stopped by this warung for lunch. It's not bad for a warung. The cuisine is local. We only tried 2 dishes.
I didn't understand why the rice was red, nasi goreng was very dry. The portions are small but the price is not high either.
Liked the fact that it was clean. Really the staff is not that friendly, they are just emotionlessüòÑ
review 2: Delicious and reasonably priced, just as the cost suggests. The place is spacious and clean, offering a delightful view of greenery and the blue sky. The vintage decor is also fascinating to behold.
review 3: The food is okay but really worth the price and the ambience is nice with the little garden and fish pond
review 4:
Sorry changed my 5 star rating to just 3, to super slow serving. My orders is served in 50 minutes (!), and I observed the other queue has the same problem, more than 40 mins serving.

The food is delicious and the price is pretty reasonable, and the place is quite cozy; a great combo for a restaurant. If not because of these, I can easily leave 1 star here.

This place is used to be my go-to place for family dinner, but not again. Unless you have abundant time for waiting, you may try this place.

----
Update 2024.

Still long wait for being served, +50 mins to get your food. There is no improvement at all from last year. I wonder if adding kitchen staffs would help?
review 5: Have eaten here a few times when in Bali. The food is always fresh and cooked well. Lots of flavour and the service is good as well and very reasonably priced.  Will definitely return again. Always busy which is a good sign they are doing things right.

name: Twenty4Seven Bed & Breakfast
address: Jl. Nuansa Udayana IX No.17, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Best place! Thanks so much to the ladies for their help & effort. Feels like family
review 2:
Horrible. Spent one night there and couldn't sleep because my room was just next to the chilling area and there was music and people speaking loud all night long.
I told it to the woman in the reception and she just told them to shut the music down, which they did for a while until they put it back. When I asked her to change my room she laughed.
After that she started speaking by phone very loud next to our room at 1 am so I don't think she cares if we can rest or not.
The only thing I ask for when I book a place to sleep is resting and here I wasn't able to do it. I can't recommend this place.
review 3: The staff is very friendly and helpful, but there is no security measures there. I lost my day backpack yesterday. I left in 15 mins unattended. The owner tried her best to help, but no results
review 4:
Lovely people to stay with..helpful and inviting..the gym is a bonus and being on the hill in jimbaran has the benefit of being cooler than some places down lower..the hammock style is comfortable and cooler again with mosquito nets supplied being a great bonus..the showers and toilets are refreshingly user friendly also
Quiet off the main with nice views
review 5:
Great price, delicious and cheap breakfast. The best thing about this place is the  people, the owner gave some fantastic advise for traveling around bali and he speaks excellent English so no worries there.

Great place to unwind for a bit before during or after your travels. Staff is friends, place is clean.

name: OYO 1200 Kencana Residence
address: Jl. Danau Tamblingan IV No.5, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Cheap room with complete facilities.
Cool AC, large bed, clean, cozy, quite, spacy bathroom.
review 2:
the staff is very unfriendly and lazy.
don't want to clean the room.
not allowed to change towels.
When you submit a complaint, the service will immediately hang up

Not recommended for the staff
review 3: Pretty Good place with comfortable sleep experience but the service so bad and rude ! Need staff who knows knowledge about hospitality!
review 4: Amazing place to stay in bali.. probably the best one. The Staff were really helpful and made the mood of the stay very homey‚ù§ Room was spacious, comfy and very clean. Highly recommend.üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª
review 5: The room was very clean. Staff is friendly. Very good value for the relatively low price. I would recommend the cafe Orbit nearby for some nice Indonesian food.

name: Villa Hening Jimbaran Bali by Island Escape Villas
address: Kori Nuansa, Harbour View, Kav. 17, Jimbaran, South Kuta, Badung Regency, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: management is very bad. they let tourists make noise from midnight until morning, parties and fireworks. doesn't respect local residents!!!
review 2: Bad review for the management, can't handle with annoying guest who make noise until morning üëé
review 3: Amazing, quiet place close to all you might need. With a gorgeous view! We enjoyed our stay in Villa Hening. Big and clean swimming pool, and nice and polite staff, I like the room style (not brand new, but looks okay)
review 4:
The room was very spacious and nite. The outside bathroom was super cute tho it could be a bit cleaner. The walk in closet could fit a large family clothes and more.
Staff are very friendly and apologised for the WiFi to be off due a cable to be down the previous day, and even borrowed their own data to be in touch with the driver. The breakfast was good and the pool area was magnificent to start our stay in Bali.
review 5: We opted a pool view room it was very big and cleaning should be improved. Room was a bit scary. Had very less options for breakfast.

name: Rumah Makan Jesica
address: Jl. Nuansa Udayana I No.33, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
My husband and I go to Jesica often - we try to go at least once a month as the service is so great and the food is incredible üç¥ü§ç

The keripik kentang are the best in Bali - we have never had a bad meal here. Prices are well balanced. It cost more than fair for the quality of food received. The atmosphere is modern, clean and pleasant. This place is so popular, no wonder it gets so busy especially during lunch rush hour.

We are very happy customers. I have read some of these negative reviews and I have to say these types of customers are never happy. If anyone asks for Indonesian home cooking food in Bali, I'll no longer point them in another direction, they will get a full Jesica recommendation.
review 2: Authentic Medanese (North Sumatra) dishes that tastes delicious, 5 star dishes
review 3: Good place if you want some medan food. Some specialties was only available on sunday. Parking was a little bit hard and place was a bit crowded but the food was very good
review 4: North sumatran cuisine. You can experience this kind of food in KL or Penang as they have same chinese background. The specialty here is kering kentang, sambal terasi, and udang (shrimp) balado.
review 5: I always love the food! Kripik kentang, buncis, nasi uduk, nasi hainan, rendang. Super tasty and affordable price. The real Medan's cuisine :)

name: Galih Kuliner
address: Taman Griya, Nuansa Kori, 654Q+925, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Best stay for try indonesian food.wonderful tempe penyet,good taste fish grilled and chicken.
Fish grilled/fried cost 45000idr.
review 2: The food is good, only the hospital is lacking and the place is a bit messy and dirty
review 3: My friend likes their ayam bakar
review 4: Great price, Delicious foods specially for the grilled fish. But not very comfort place for chit chat.
review 5:
Probably some of the best sambal I've had in Bali. The prices are great for what you get but do note that for a foreigner, the fish may be on the small side. Recommend to get a side of rice and a app.

Note, you need to write down your order at the middle cart so write clearly.

name: YoriMichi
address: Jl. Danau Batur Raya No.27, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Stumbled across this amazing Japanese owned gem for dinner. Wasn‚Äôt sure at first but ended up with the most authentic Japanese home meal selection! None around in the entire Bukit (besides some washed up overpriced Japanese dishes here and there) so now saves us the daunting trip to Kuta for decent Japanese. Great value for money and the quality won‚Äôt disappoint- a must visit!
review 2: My favorite place for japanese home-cooked dining. Let me tell you about the star of the show: the Tenzaru Soba. Picture chilled buckwheat noodles, perfectly cooked and served with a dipping sauce that made my taste buds dance with joy. And let's not forget the crispy tempura that accompanied the noodles, adding a delightful crunch to each bite. It was a simple yet satisfying dish that left me craving more.
review 3:
Yorimichi restaurant has a homey like setting. With outdoor and indoor seating, they also have a private room.

Shio ramen, fresh salmon sashimi, yakitori were our usual pick in this restaurant. Yorimichi also serve beer and bali artisan beer like Bremen.

One of my go to Japanese restaurant in Bali!
review 4:
Pros:
The empty plates mean is delicioussssssss........ üòçüòçüòç yummy!
The place is cosy

Con: the waiting time for the food can be up to 2 hour for 1 set fo sushie
review 5:
The foods are so delicious and taste so authentic of Japanese food.
The price is fair enough with the food quality. The staff is friendly and helpful.
Serving time is moderate.
Overall is recommended.üëç

name: Ayam Kremes Panjer
address: Jl. Nuansa Utama No.99, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
First time try here cause always looks crowded everytime passed by. Not impressive at all.
Sambal pecak was too spicy and super oily, chicken very small, the worst condition is that only has 2 fan available, even though open space but still feel super hot. Yes, imagined eat spicy foods and no fan supported (sweaty not comfortable at all). Some people smoking in the restaurant area, making it more even even worse.
review 3: Decent taste for a mainstream foodie. The foods are as much as the price. I mean, if you want eat more, you will have to pay more. With Rp 13,000 you will get an Ayam Kremes (that time I got fried chicken's leg), and a plate of rice. That's kinda cheap, but still I didn't get enough. You can try to have a meal here!
review 4: first time eating at this place and was a little surprised because the package with all you can eat rice was given very much compared to other kremes chicken chilies
review 5: Cheap, fast and delicius restaurant. I love ayam kremes saos asam manis here, you can add rice and ice tea as much as you want hehe. I love it

name: Coco House
address: Jl. Nuansa Utama V No.11, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
The place have a problems, but everytime we say something to them the answer always yes but in the reality they never do anything to fix it. Also they up the price every 2-4 months in a year, normally in Indonesia they do it once a year only. Because i already in Indonesia for many years. Also if they wanna fix something or have a problems with electricity or water or building, they never let you know, until you find out by your self. No coordinations with the worker here and people who's staying.

But once you say to pick up the money, they will be in front of your door less than 1 minute. Faster than the flash.

But for the location is really good, so quiet most of the day, near to the shops around.
review 2: The place is good... there is a view because next to it is empty open land. The rooms are special, like apartments, the interior is well designed and looks luxurious.  Standard prices and friendly Owners...
review 3: Nice place. It's not a guest house, it's looks like apartments. Btw it's really big, including: small hall, kitchen, 2 balcony, big bedroom, 1 hall, big wardrobe and very bright and also big bathroom. Really nice place for rest and living.
review 4: Room is very cozy with beautiful view of bali  and they clean your room every monday which is nice.
review 5: Good price, good view, free wifi, and they clean your room every monday

name: Nasi Uduk Betawi Mak Tentong
address: taman griya, Jl. Perum Tropic Residence No.D1, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Didn't expect the food to be this tasty. The small house terrace offers authentic nasi uduk betawi served in beautifully done plating. Very affordable for students üëç
review 2: A gem! Ordered their food a couple times, and finally tried on site. Nasi uduk was so good! Service was friendly, very good pricing too.
review 3: This place serve authentic Betawi food. The price is affordable and the taste is good.
review 4: If you are in Bali, you should try this Nasi Uduk. You can directly go there or order by app. Mantap cing !
review 5:
Very nice food. We ordered it on Gojek to our hotel several mornings for breakfast.

The nasi ayam bakar is a perfect light breakfast, also try the various extra dishes such as rempeyeh kacang, and build your own breakfast table (or any other time of the day).

The delivery and packaging was neat and quick, which we appreciated a lot. Terima kasih!

name: Bakmie Keriting 78
address: Jl. Danau Buyan Raya Perumahan Taman Griya No.2, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Delicious food of Chindo Medanese style.
Spacious place to dine in.
I asked my Bakmi Keriting Pangsit without green vegie and it came as I requested.

Recommended!!!
review 2: One of best bakmie in Bali. Always nic3 to dine there. Semua makanan recommended!
review 3: Contrary to other people, i think their bakmi is just okay, although it's not too bad either. It is just i don't find it is extraordinary. The place is pretty spacious though, i think the place is located on their own house front. They sell pork bakmi btw. Place is pretty clean but sometimes in this scorching Bali, we just need an air conditioner.
review 4: small and simple noodle resto inside the Taman Griya residential area, but don't let the look deceive you, it has the most delicious chicken noodles in town, price is affordable and cheaper compared to its competitors, services are decent, the only disappointment is the portion is too small
review 5: The search for good pork noodle in Jimbaran area is over. I think this is one of the best in Bali. Authentic bakmi keriting! Menu is simple - but that's enough! A must when you're in this area.

name: Villa Jepun Bali
address: 654M+GJ3, Jl. Bougenville Boulevard, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Nice place to stay,  we had private pool inside
review 2: Nice place if you want for take a rest.
review 3: Great for a chill time with fams, and small groups of friends.

name: Warung Bu Nur JIMBARAN
address: Jimbaran, South Kuta, Badung Regency, Bali 80361, Indonesia

name: CV. YASATRANS
address: Perumahan Nuansa Udayana No. 18, Lingkungan Taman Griya, Kuta Selatan, Jl. Nuansa Udayana, Jimbaran, Badung, Badung Regency, Bali 80364, Indonesia

name: W home stay
address: Jl. Nuansa Utama IV, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Jimbaran, South Kuta, bali, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: I stayed there for 2 nights, the people working there really friendly and everything inside the room was clean. The best so far üëç
review 2: Loved the design, very clean and spacious room too. Love the environment of the hotel, peaceful and good security system.
review 3: This place it was so good for me I stay there for 15 days the room it‚Äôs big clean  and so close to uluwatu so if you are a surfer it be good for you
review 4: Nice view and good service. Recommended

name: Villa Herry
address: Jl. Nuansa Udayana Taman Griya Jimbaran No.2A, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
OK villa.  Nice enough rooms. But, the whole place is quite dirty and is infested with ants, cockroaches, and RATS!!! The owners place anti insect pellets around the house to repel them but they caused us headaches and are extremely unpleasant.

We also asked to check out an hour late and the said it would cost the same price as a whole night (350k)! We decided against it, but then we waited over half an hour for them to turn up and collect the keys and they never arrived. When we messaged them they told us to leave the keys in the lock box. Very cheeky behaviour!
review 2: Big villa with 4 rooms, big pool, nice and quiet neighborhood in the housing complex, friendly and helpful service
review 3: This villa is amazing, comfortable, the surrounding environment is not noisy, and it is very convenient to get to dining places
review 4: An excellent option for a group holiday. We all really liked it, recommended it and noticed it again
review 5: The villa is big and comfy, perfect for big families. It also has parking space for 2 cars üëå

name: Kei's Residence
address: Jl. Nuansa Udayana Utara VI No.31, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Thank you Khesia for the hospitality! Always in touch üòç
The house has a positive atmosphere ) very comfortable and pleasant for a long stay . There is everything you need, soap accessories, coffee, etc. The presence of a washing machine is a big plus)
I'm not ready to give all my clothes to laundry)))
Wonderful rooftop and beautiful views. Good geographical location .
I definitely recommend itüß°üî•
review 2:
We lived here for 3 months on the top floor and it was the best accommodation we had on the island.

Many small things created a truly cozy atmosphere in the room!

There is a washing machine on the ground floor, so you can use it at any time.

Large kitchen with 2 refrigerators and clean water in large bottles.

On the top floor you can relax or have a party with friends.

Separate parking with a gate makes life safer

And the main advantage of this residence is the owner Keisha. She was very kind to us and never turned down any of our requests! She is very kind and we ended up becoming friends!
review 3:
I stayed at Kei's Residence long-term and it developed to be a new home for me. The room is really cozy with the lovely decorations and a cozy big bed. In general the house is well equipped with a kitchen that has everything you need and a beautiful roof terrace. Everything is cleaned twice a week with towels and bed sheets changed weekly. Kehsia is a lovely person herself, always willing to help and always responding quickly. When you would like to live in an area which is more local with many possibilities to eat local and great food it's the best place to stay. Additionally, from this place you can go to every beach within maximum 30 minutes.
All in all I would highly recommend staying here, especially for long-term guests. There is nothing you miss, and if there should be Kenias will help.

Thank you so much for having me and being a great host!
review 4:
This place became my home for 3 happy months! I had a room at the top of the house and view was amazing! Also there‚Äôre everything you may need such kettle,  fridge, iron, washing machine etc. Laundry is in 10 meters from the house, fitness centre with swimming pool is in 5 mins of walking. It‚Äôs not a touristic place so you can‚Äôt find fashionable cafe and restaurants nearby. But food in local warungs is so delicious! And Keisha is the best host!
Thank you‚ù§Ô∏è
review 5: A great place to stay! Thank you for the warmth and comfort ‚ù§Ô∏è I want to come back here!

name: Pondok Satria
address: Taman Griya, Jl. Danau Tamblingan VI No.66, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia

name: Medan Food
address: Jl. Danau Batur Raya No.41, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Plastic in food.

Would recommend steering clear of this restaurant. Food is quite tasty but plastic keeps showing up in food.

If this was a restaurant in Australia, it would be shut down. Finding plastic pieces in food is completely unacceptable. And after reading the reviews on here, I see that it's a regular occurrence. Which would suggest that there is a lack of caring when preparing the food. If it was only one time and they learnt from it, everyone makes mistakes. But the fact that it's happened over and over again. It's just not worth the risk to eat there. The food could be the best tasting food in the world, but if there's a risk it will shorten your life?

Not worth it
review 2: We bought this on Grab and it was disgusting. There was a fried piece of plastic in our food and the taste was horrendous, congrats on my first bad review. Worst 100k ever spent
review 3:
Hawker stalls that sell snacks such as cakwe and ronde.
Taste very good and the price is also affordable at 3,000 idr / piece
review 4: Delicious and clean food with a reasonable prices. A must try and recommended.
review 5:
Not recommended
Owner attitude worst
No smile, no warm welcome
No hospitality at all
Bad work management( no first come first serve)
